{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:48:11.428328", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 1 super-spine (AS 65000), 2 spines (AS 65100, 65101), 2 leaves (AS 65200, 65201), and 2 hosts (pc_0_0 on 10.0.0.0/24, pc_0_1 on 10.0.1.0/24). EBGP-only fabric; interconnects on 172.16.0.0/16 /31 links.\\n- Goal: Assess network health, identify anomalies, localize faults, and determine root cause (no remediation proposed).\\n\\nKey Findings\\n\\n1) End-to-end reachability\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 100% loss with Destination Host Unreachable, originating from 172.16.0.7 (leaf_router_0_1 uplink). Evidence:\\n  - PING from pc_0_0: “From 172.16.0.7 Destination Host Unreachable” (4/4).\\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: immediate failure “Network is unreachable.”\\n\\n2) Host access-layer state\\n- pc_0_1\\n  - Interface eth0 is DOWN; no routes present.\\n    - ip addr: eth0 state DOWN, inet 10.0.1.2/24.\\n    - ip route: empty.\\n  - Ping to default gateway 10.0.1.1 fails “Network is unreachable.”\\n- pc_0_0\\n  - Interface eth0 is UP, ip 10.0.0.2/24 with default via 10.0.0.1.\\n  - Can reach its leaf SVI: pc_0_0 -> 10.0.0.1 succeeds.\\n\\n3) Leaf L3 gateways and ARP\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (gateway for 10.0.1.0/24)\\n  - Interface eth2 10.0.1.1/24 is UP.\\n  - ARP for 10.0.1.2 remains INCOMPLETE:\\n    - ip neigh on leaf_router_0_1: “10.0.1.2 INCOMPLETE.”\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.1.2 returns “Destination Host Unreachable” (cannot resolve ARP on directly connected segment).\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (gateway for 10.0.0.0/24)\\n  - Interface eth2 10.0.0.1/24 is UP.\\n  - pc_0_0 can reach leaf_router_0_1’s SVI:\\n    - pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1: success, 0% loss.\\n    - spine_router_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1: success, 0% loss.\\n    - (One timed-out ping from leaf_router_0_0 to 10.0.1.1 observed, but subsequent cross-fabric tests from pc_0_0 and spine confirm reachability to 10.0.1.1; no persistent fabric issue indicated.)\\n\\n4) Control-plane health (BGP/Routes)\\n- All EBGP sessions are established across the fabric:\\n  - Leaves (65200/65201) have 2 neighbors each (both spines) with State/PfxRcd = 1 per neighbor.\\n  - Spines have 3 neighbors each (super-spine + both leaves); routes present to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n  - Super-spine has 2 neighbors (both spines) with PfxRcd = 2 from each.\\n- Route tables:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: has BGP route to 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (towards spine_router_0_0).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: has BGP route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\\n  - Both spines have BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via the correct leaf-facing interfaces.\\n- Conclusion: Control plane is converged and advertising the expected /24 host networks; no BGP anomalies detected.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- End-to-end host connectivity between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 is broken due to failure on the 10.0.1.0/24 access segment:\\n  - pc_0_1 NIC is down and has no routing table.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 cannot resolve ARP for 10.0.1.2 (incomplete ARP), causing ICMP Host Unreachable to be sent upstream.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty component: pc_0_1 (host) or its immediate L2 link to leaf_router_0_1 (leaf eth2 <-> host eth0). The rest of the fabric (leaves-spines-super spine) is healthy.\\n- Fabric transport is functional, demonstrated by successful pings to the 10.0.1.1 SVI from multiple other nodes.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- pc_0_1’s interface eth0 is administratively or operationally down. This results in:\\n  - No L2 adjacency on 10.0.1.0/24.\\n  - No ARP resolution for 10.0.1.2 on leaf_router_0_1.\\n  - pc_0_1 lacking default route and unable to reach its gateway.\\n  - Upstream ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” responses when attempting to reach pc_0_1 from elsewhere.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Traffic to/from host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2) is disrupted.\\n- All other fabric routing and intra-fabric reachability to leaf SVIs is normal. The issue is isolated to the access edge of subnet 10.0.1.0/24 at pc_0_1., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='e6d4e970-05cb-48ce-8b29-f6aece57ee9d'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
